# 6. Exploratory Data Analysis

## 6.1 Industry AUM Trends

Analysis of Assets Under Management (AUM) revealed consistent growth in the mutual fund industry.

Major observations:

* Industry AUM increased steadily over time.
* Large AMCs dominated industry assets.
* Growth was supported by increasing SIP participation.

[Insert AUM Trend Chart]

---

## 6.2 Fund Category Analysis

Category-level analysis showed:

* Equity funds attracted significant investor interest.
* Debt funds exhibited lower volatility.
* Hybrid categories provided balanced risk-return characteristics.

[Insert Category Analysis Chart]

---

## 6.3 Investor Demographics

Investor analysis indicated:

* Younger investors showed greater SIP participation.
* Urban investors contributed higher transaction volumes.
* Different age groups displayed distinct investment behaviors.

